{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872152381,"sessionID":"ses_285c5a73dffe6YuW2ZXWi3FUcT","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3a841200128k1jzz9PllN85","messageID":"msg_d7a3a6f020013BiZdsj5n1TIcD","sessionID":"ses_285c5a73dffe6YuW2ZXWi3FUcT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_19cd71555a1445b69aec384e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI Publish Command Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** L  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Foundation & Models ✓\n11: \n12: - [x] **T1.1** Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with publish-related fields\n13:   - Fields: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`, `version`, `region`\n14:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/metadata_models.py`\n15:   - Verify: Model validates correctly with test fixtures\n16: \n17: - [x] **T1.2** Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata()` and `save_metadata()`\n18:   - Support multiple metadata file names: `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`\n19:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n20:   - Verify: Loads/saves metadata correctly in test workspace\n21: \n22: - [x] **T1.3** Add publish-related CLI options to `PublishRuntime`\n23:   - Options: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n24:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n25:   - Verify: Options are accepted and passed through runtime methods\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Phase 2: Core Runtime Implementation ✓\n30: \n31: - [x] **T2.1** Implement `PublishRuntime.publish()` method\n32:   - Load metadata, prepare image, delegate to provider, update metadata\n33:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n34:   - Verify: Returns `Dict[str, Any]` with agent info\n35: \n36: - [x] **T2.2** Implement `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` dispatcher\n37:   - Route to `_prepare_local_image()` or `_prepare_cloud_image()` based on `metadata.build_mode`\n38:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n39:   - Verify: Correct routing logic\n40: \n41: - [x] **T2.3** Implement `_prepare_local_image()` for local build mode\n42:   - Validate `image_url` is provided\n43:   - Push image to registry using `DockerService.push_image()` if credentials available\n44:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n45:   - Verify: Returns `image_url`, pushes image when credentials provided\n46: \n47: - [x] **T2.4** Implement `_prepare_cloud_image()` for cloud build mode\n48:   - Construct image URL from `cloud_provider`, `agent_name`, `version`\n49:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n50:   - Verify: Returns formatted image URL string\n51: \n52: - [x] **T2.5** Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n53:   - Create `AgentCubeProvider` instance\n54:   - Deploy `AgentRuntime` CR with required fields: `workloadManagerURL`, `routerURL`, readiness probe\n55:   - Generate `session_id`, `agent_id`\n56:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n57:   - Verify: Returns dict with `status`, `agent_name`, `namespace`, `session_id`, `agent_id`\n58: \n59: - [x] **T2.6** Implement `_publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n60:   - Create `KubernetesProvider` instance\n61:   - Deploy `Deployment` + `Service` (optionally `NodePort`)\n62:   - Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767)\n63:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n64:   - Verify: Returns dict with deployment info\n65: \n66: - [x] **T2.7** Implement `_update_publish_metadata()` to persist publish results\n67:   - Update: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`\n68:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n69:   - Verify: Metadata file updated after publish\n70: \n71: - [x] **T2.8** Implement `_generate_session_id()` helper\n72:   - Generate 32-character alphanumeric string using `secrets.choice()`\n73:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n74:   - Verify: Returns unique ID on each call\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## Phase 3: Provider Services ✓\n79: \n80: - [x] **T3.1** Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n81:   - Create/replace `AgentRuntime` CR in K8s\n82:   - Handle 409 conflict (update existing)\n83:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n84:   - Verify: CR created/updated in cluster\n85: \n86: - [x] **T3.2** Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s naming rules\n87:   - Lowercase, replace non-alphanumeric with `-`, max 63 chars\n88:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n89:   - Verify: Produces valid K8s resource names\n90: \n91: - [x] **T3.3** Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for standard K8s deployment\n92:   - Create `Deployment`, `Service` (ClusterIP or NodePort)\n93:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n94:   - Verify: Resources created in cluster\n95: \n96: - [x] **T3.4** Add error handling for missing K8s config\n97:   - Try kubeconfig, then in-cluster config\n98:   - Raise `RuntimeError` with helpful message if both fail\n99:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`, `k8s_provider.py`\n100:   - Verify: Clear error message when K8s unavailable\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## Phase 4: CLI Integration ✓\n105: \n106: - [x] **T4.1** Add `publish` command to CLI with Typer\n107:   - All options from T1.3 as `@app.command()` parameters\n108:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n109:   - Verify: `agentcube publish --help` shows all options\n110: \n111: - [x] **T4.2** Implement CLI progress UI for publish\n112:   - Use `rich.progress` spinner during publish\n113:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n114:   - Verify: Spinner displays during operation\n115: \n116: - [x] **T4.3** Format and display publish results\n117:   - Show: `Agent ID`, `Endpoint`, `Namespace`, `Provider`\n118:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n119:   - Verify: Output is clear and readable\n120: \n121: - [x] **T4.4** Implement consistent error handling\n122:   - Use `_handle_error()` helper with verbose traceback option\n123:   - Exit code 1 on failure\n124:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n125:   - Verify: Errors display clearly, verbose mode shows traceback\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## Phase 5: Validation & Edge Cases\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T5.1** Validate `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` are present for `agentcube` provider\n132:   - Check metadata or environment variables\n133:   - Raise `ValueError` with helpful message if missing\n134:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n135:   - Verify: Clear error when URLs missing\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T5.2** Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767) for K8s provider\n138:   - Already implemented in `_publish_k8s()`, add CLI-level validation\n139:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n140:   - Verify: Rejects invalid ports before runtime call\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.3** Handle existing AgentRuntime CR gracefully (update vs create)\n143:   - Already implemented via 409 handling in `AgentCubeProvider`\n144:   - Add logging to indicate update vs create\n145:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n146:   - Verify: Logs indicate whether CR was created or updated\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T5.4** Handle image push failures gracefully\n149:   - Catch `DockerService` exceptions, re-raise with context\n150:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n151:   - Verify: Clear error message on push failure\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T5.5** Validate metadata file exists before publish\n154:   - Check for `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml`\n155:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n156:   - Verify: Early error if metadata missing\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## Phase 6: Testing\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T6.1** Unit test `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()`\n163:   - Test with/without `image_url`, with/without credentials\n164:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n165:   - Verify: Correct image URL returned, push called when expected\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T6.2** Unit test `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()`\n168:   - Test various `cloud_provider`, `version` combinations\n169:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n170:   - Verify: Correct image URL format\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T6.3** Unit test `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n173:   - Mock `AgentCubeProvider`, verify CR spec\n174:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n175:   - Verify: Correct provider call, session_id generated\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T6.4** Unit test `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()`\n178:   - Mock `KubernetesProvider`, verify deployment params\n179:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n180:   - Verify: Correct provider call, node_port validated\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T6.5** Integration test: publish to K8s (mock cluster)\n183:   - Use `kind` or `kindless` K8s cluster\n184:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_publish_integration.py`\n185:   - Verify: CR/deployment created, metadata updated\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T6.6** CLI test: `agentcube publish --help`\n188:   - Verify all options documented\n189:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n190:   - Verify: Help text accurate\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T6.7** Error case: missing `workload_manager_url`\n193:   - Verify clear error message\n194:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n195:   - Verify: `ValueError` raised with helpful message\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T6.8** Error case: invalid `node_port`\n198:   - Verify validation